# Contributing to MusicBox

ğŸ‘ğŸ‰ First off, thanks for taking the time to contribute! ğŸ‰ğŸ‘

The following is a set of guidelines for contributing to MusicBox. These are just guidelines, not rules, so use your best judgment and feel free to propose changes to this document in a pull request.

## Code of Conduct

This project and everyone participating in it are governed by the [Code of Conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). By participating, you are expected to uphold this code. Please report unacceptable behavior to [contact@musicbox.com].

## How Can I Contribute?

### Reporting Bugs

- Before creating a bug report, check if the issue has already been reported in the [GitHub issues](https://github.com/monokaijs/musicbox/issues).
- If you're unable to find an open issue addressing the problem, open a new one. Be sure to include a clear title and description, as much relevant information as possible, and steps to reproduce the issue.

### Suggesting Enhancements

- Before creating a feature request, check if it has already been suggested in the [GitHub issues](https://github.com/monokaijs/musicbox/issues).
- If you don't find an open issue related to your suggestion, feel free to open a new one. Clearly describe the feature you'd like to see, and discuss it with the community.

### Pull Requests

- Before you start working on an issue, make sure it's assigned to you or that you let others know you're working on it to avoid duplication of efforts.
- Fork the repository, create a branch, and work on your changes.
- Ensure your code follows the project's coding standards.
- Make your pull request informative, including a clear title and description of your changes.
- Be open to feedback and be willing to make changes if necessary.

## Development Setup

1. Fork the repository and clone your fork locally.
2. Install dependencies: `npm install`
3. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feature-xyz`
4. Make your changes and test thoroughly.
5. Commit your changes: `git commit -m "Add new feature"`
6. Push to your fork: `git push origin feature-xyz`
7. Create a pull request to the `main` branch of the original repository.

## License

By contributing to MusicBox, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the [MIT License](LICENSE).

